  <title translate="true">CRCH: Conduit Recharge Pane</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">CRCH: Conduit Recharge Pane</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">CRCH: Conduit Recharge</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> pane is on the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MODFLOW_Features_Tab" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">MODFLOW Features</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> tab of the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Object_Properties_Dialog_Box" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Object Properties</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">This pane is only visible if the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="CFP_Conduit_Flow_Process" styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Conduit Flow Process</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> is selected and </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="CFP_Conduit_Flow_Process" anchor="Mode" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">individual conduits are simulated</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="RCH_Recharge_Package_Pane" styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Recharge</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> package is selected and </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="CFP_Conduit_Flow_Process" anchor="ConduitRecharge" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">conduit recharge</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> is selected.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The data that can be specified for the Conduit Recharge package are the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Starting time</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Ending time</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, and </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Recharge fraction</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true">. &#160;The </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Recharge fraction</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> is the fraction of the recharge in a cell that should be diverted to a conduit node. It should be between 0 and 1.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Starting time</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> and </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Ending time</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> are explained in the help for the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MODFLOW_Features_Tab" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">MODFLOW Features</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> tab.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">When conduit recharge is displayed by coloring the grid all the cells enclosed or intersected by the object will be colored even though only cells that are actually conduit nodes will have recharge diverted to them.</text></para>
  </body>
